# AI Behavior Rules

## Code Quality

- Always write clean, readable, production-level code
- Prefer readability over cleverness
- No unnecessary abstractions — if it can be done simply, do it simply
- No over-engineering — this is an assignment, not a distributed system
- Ask for clarification if requirements are unclear before writing code
- Do not create files that are not needed

## When Writing Frontend Code

- Always handle loading states and error states in every component
- Never put fetch calls directly in components, always use src/api/ layer
- Never use any or unknown TypeScript types without a comment explaining why

## When Writing Backend Code

- Never put business logic in route handlers, always delegate to services/
- Always use try/except with proper HTTP status codes
- Always validate with Pydantic before processing
- Always use async/await for route handlers

## LLM Calls

- No LangChain, no LangGraph, ever
- All prompts are strings stored in server/prompts/ folder
- Always validate and parse LLM responses before returning to frontend
- Always have a fallback if LLM returns unexpected format
